"1. Please keep a short distance between the drone, LNT device, and the app. Make sure there is no obstruction between devices. 2. Keep the remote controller’s antennas pointed towards the drone to ensure optimal signal strength. 3. Check if the networked LNT device is functioning properly, or restart it, and then reconnect your mobile device to its hotspot."

"1. Keep the drone, central node device, and app close to each other, ensuring there are no obstructions between them. 2. Always orient the antenna of the remote controller toward the drone for optimal signal strength. 3. Check if the local network terminal devices are functioning properly, or restart them and reconnect to the hotspot. 4. If local network issues persist, switch to the cellular network link for transmission. After switching, the HD map data will be retransmitted."

If both the drone and remote controller support cellular networks, you can complete networking by binding the remote controller to the drone.
If the above conditions are not met, please follow these steps to network:
Turn on the remote controller and connect the drone to the remote controller’s network.
When the drone is on, press and hold the power button for more than 10 seconds. When you hear a beep, the third light will start blinking yellow.

"Please place the drone in an open area and power it up. Put the drone in networking mode according to how it is powered up.
Option 1: If you power up the drone by long-pressing the battery power button for more than 5 seconds, quickly short-press the battery power button 3 times after power-up, and when the ESC indicators turn blinking yellow, the drone enters networking mode.
Option 2: If you power up the drone by long-pressing the power button until the battery indicators blink and then long-pressing the battery power button, long press the battery power button for more than 10 seconds after power-up, and when the ESC indicators turn blinking yellow, the drone enters networking mode."
Wait for about 10 seconds until the drone’s yellow ESC indicator or the third light (yellow) on the remote controller goes off, and the remote controller and drone are connected.
"After turning on and adding the XRTK6 Pro, tap to enter the device networking screen. Select the drone, your mobile device, and ACS4 (if needed), and connect them to the XRTK6 Pro's hotspot."
Tap to enter SRC5’s networking screen. Set the Networking Mode to AP Mode, and select a drone or XRTK7 for networking.
"After turning on and adding the XRTK7, tap to enter the Device Networking screen to connect the drone, this device, and ACS4 (if needed) to XRTK7's Wi-Fi."

Purchasing XAG V40 2021 Agricultural UAV or XAG P80 2021 Agricultural UAV from our dealers, either recommended by sales agencies or visit directly, may receive a pesticide voucher of corresponding credit. Upon purchasing and adding the UAV to the XAG Go App, the pesticide voucher will be posted to the XAG account where the device is added. User may view such vouchers via Me>Service>Pesticide Voucher in the XAG Go App.

Please visit any pesticide sales outlet linked to your pesticide voucher within its validity period, and purchase pesticides with an XAG Pesticide Identification Code. You may then open the XAG Go App, find your voucher via Me>Service>Pesticide Voucher>Scan to Activate, and scan the Pesticide Identification Code to have your voucher activated.

After operations are completed using the linked XAG V40 2021 Agricultural UAV or XAG P80 2021 Agricultural UAV, the activated pesticide allowance will be automatically converted into a withdrawable one based on the actual operation area at a standard of CNY 2 per mu. Such pesticide allowance would be automatically deposited to the user’s account and could be viewed and withdrawn via Me>Service>Pesticide Voucher>Withdraw.

When the drone is transferred, user is no longer allowed to activate the pesticide voucher with this drone. Already activated pesticide allowance will be voided, but the amount withdrawable will still be valid.

Granule container connection error. Please try one of the following: 1. Check if the sensor module of the granule container is intact. 2. Check if the sensor module of the granule container is properly connected to the payload cable hub. 3. Check if the indicator is flashing green. There is no indicator on if abnormal power supply of the sensor module occurs. Flashing green means the granule container fails to establish communication with the spreading system and the sensor needs to be replaced. 4. Please check or replace the payload cable hub if the indicator remains solid green and the granule container is still offline after replacing the sensor module. 5. If all else fails, please contact customer service or technical support.
